The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 October is 87,979 (10,140.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 October, there were 4,090 new confirmed cases (471.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 October, there were 2,854 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 43% (1,236 extra cases).
